        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 2:15PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Salisbury, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Linwood, Gordontown, High Rock Boat Dock Marina, Nc Wildlife Access
Boat Launch, High Rock Lake Marina &amp; Campground, Lexington, High Rock
Lake, and High Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
